leftPanelData.eventName: Tampere Philharmonic Orchestra: Season opening: Ode to Joy

fullEventData.name: Tampere Philharmonic Orchestra: Season opening: Ode to Joy
fullEventData.description: Tampere Philharmonic's season begins with Sebastian Fagerlund’s orchestral whirlwind Ignite and Ludwig van Beethoven’s Ninth Symphony, a timeless symbol of joy and universal friendship.

leftPanelData.eventName: Tampere Philharmonic Orchestra: Verses of the Heart

fullEventData.name: Tampere Philharmonic Orchestra: Verses of the Heart
fullEventData.description: Stravinsky’s Petrushka leaps between styles, while Rachmaninoff’s symphony overflows with melody. In this concert evening featuring two works, the orchestra itself shines as the soloist.

leftPanelData.eventName: Tampere Philharmonic Orchestra: The Magic of Mozart

fullEventData.name: Tampere Philharmonic Orchestra: The Magic of Mozart
fullEventData.description: Two world-class artists specializing in Viennese Classicism—conductor Jonathan Cohen and pianist Kristian Bezuidenhout—dedicate the evening to the masterworks of W. A. Mozart.

leftPanelData.eventName: Afternoon of Fauns: Up and Away!

fullEventData.name: Afternoon of Fauns: Up and Away!
fullEventData.description: Afternoon of Fauns takes you on a soaring journey. Expect a medley of highlights, from virtuosic solos and lush, romantic delicacies to an all-out disco finale to the beat of the ’90s.

leftPanelData.eventName: Tampere Philharmonic Orchestra: In the Embrace of Rosenkavalier

fullEventData.name: Tampere Philharmonic Orchestra: In the Embrace of Rosenkavalier
fullEventData.description: A dazzling concerto, nostalgic waltzes, and a lush modern soundscape—rising conductor Kristian Sallinen leads a colourful concert with cellist Senja Rummukainen as the soloist.

leftPanelData.eventName: Tampere Philharmonic Orchestra: Echoes of Kalevala

fullEventData.name: Tampere Philharmonic Orchestra: Echoes of Kalevala
fullEventData.description: Echoes of Kalevala is an audiovisual concert experience celebrating the epic’s 190th anniversary. The performance blends the ancient Finno-Ugric tradition of rune singing with echoes of pop music.

leftPanelData.eventName: Tampere Philharmonic Orchestra: King of the French Horn

fullEventData.name: Tampere Philharmonic Orchestra: King of the French Horn
fullEventData.description: There are thousands of horn players, but only one Stefan Dohr. The principal horn of Berlin Philharmonic shines as the soloist in a new concerto framed by Sibelius' Tapiola and Brahms' Symphony No 1.

leftPanelData.eventName: Afternoon of Fauns: Shivers and Glimmers

fullEventData.name: Afternoon of Fauns: Shivers and Glimmers
fullEventData.description: The haunting mystery of Dmitri Shostakovich’s music pierces deep into the soul. His Eighth String Quartet, born in the ruins of Dresden, is a bittersweet danse macabre on lost humanity’s grave.

leftPanelData.eventName: Tampere Philharmonic Orchestra: Independence Day concert – Northern Song

fullEventData.name: Tampere Philharmonic Orchestra: Independence Day concert – Northern Song
fullEventData.description: The Independence Day concert features highlights of Finnish music, from Sibelius’s Finlandia and Rautavaara’s Cantus Arcticus to a new work by Tampere-based composer Petri Nieminen.

leftPanelData.eventName: Afternoon of Fauns: Echoes on the Plains

fullEventData.name: Afternoon of Fauns: Echoes on the Plains
fullEventData.description: Some of the most beloved works arise from vast, open landscapes: Dvořák’s quartet reflects the peaceful expanse of the prairie, while Sallinen’s variations echo the deep melancholy of a folk song.

fullEventData.description: Tampere Philharmonic performs Edward Elgar’s The Dream of Gerontius together with outstanding soloists and choir. Single tickets of spring 2026 season series concerts will go on sale later in Autumn.
